article.headline: Boise State 70, Idaho 67
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Jason Ellis scored 23 points as Boise State beat Idaho 70-67 Saturday. Jermaine Blackburn had 12 points and nine rebounds for Boise State (4-2), which beat Idaho for the eighth straight time. Idaho (0-6) made just one field goal during the final 6:31 of play and Boise State rallied to outscore the Vandals 14-5 during that time. The Vandals moved within three points, 67-64, on a 3-point basket by Dillon Higdon with 21 seconds left, but Blackburn made three of four free-throw attempts to secure the victory. Higdon had two opportunities to tie the game in the closing seconds, but both of his long, off-balance 3-point attempts missed. Ellis made 10 of 12 shots from the field in the game and was perfect in three free-throw attempts. Coby Karl added 16 points and Franco Harris 13 for the Broncos, who swept the annual home-and-home series with Idaho. Boise State topped Idaho 76-66 Nov. 19 in the season-opener for both teams. Idaho's starting guard trio of Tanoris Shepard, Dandrick Jones and Higdon combined to score 46 points and shoot 58 percent from the field for Idaho. The Vandals shots just 40 percent from the free-throw line, however, and made just six of 16 free-throw attempts in the second half. The Broncos committed 14 of their 16 turnovers in a first half that saw them trail by as many as 12 points with eight minutes gone and by seven points at halftime. The Vandals start a season 0-6 for the first time since 1939-40. That Idaho team lost 11 straight games to begin the year.
